Assignment#1¶

IE360 Spring-22¶

Aim

To see whether saving and borrowing money habits of Turkish people are affected by USD/TRY rate and interest rate it is denoted in EVDS as Consumer Loan.

Also, checking whether there is a corrolation between zam search in Google and saving and borrowing money habits.

Data Sources Used for Assignment

1-) Electronic Data Delivery System

  • Surveys / Probability of saving money
  • Surveys / Probability of borrowing money
  • Exchange rates / USD/TRY rate
  • Interest Statistics / Consumer Loan

2-) Google Trends

  • "zam" search in Turkey

These data sources indicates the period between 2014-02 and 2022-03. Each data source is in monthly period

Data Manipulation¶

In [3]:
# Preparation data
data.Date=pd.to_datetime(data.Date,format="%Y-%m")
data=data[data.Date.dt.year>=2014]

# Preparation data1
data1.rename(columns={"Month":"Date", "zam: (Turkey)":"zam"}, inplace=True)
data1.Date=pd.to_datetime(data1.Date,format="%Y-%m")
data1=data1[data1.Date.dt.year>=2014]
data1.reset_index(drop=True,inplace=True)

In code part above data used after 2014 because it is obvious that for financial statistics of Turkey are changed very fast after that date. I want to compare today's current picture with more similar data. It is the same for Google Trends search. Also, it is obivous that technology consumption is exponentially growing and more data is available recent dates, so I prefer data after 2014.

As seen above Date columns are adjusted on year-month base. Then, My datasets are ready to further.

Data Visualization¶

Comparison of Borrowing and Saving Money Habits¶

In [5]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
fig.set_size_inches(20,8)

sns.set(style="whitegrid")
data.plot(x="Date",y=["The probability of borrowing money","The probability of saving"],ax=ax)
ax.set_title("Comparison of Saving and Borrowing Habits of Turkish People")
ax.set_xlabel("Date")
ax.set_ylabel("Probability(%)")
plt.show()

First milestone is having a look to target attributes. As seen graph above probability of borrowing money and saving money have a relationship. When I decided to search saving money and borrowing money probabilities I was expecting that they are negatively correlated. However, I was wrong they seem to have positive correlation. When discussing seperately Borrowing Money trend tends to be increasing in recent 2-3 years. Also, I could not realize any obvious seasonality in this graph. On the other hand, Saving Money trend seems to be distributed around 22.5% and an increase observed in 2021. Also, it does not show any seasonality,too. Maybe, checking autocorrelation graphs gives more better result for seasonality.

In further sections, comparison of these 2 attributes with other attriubes will be visualized.

Yearly Graphs of the Attributes ( Saving and Borrowing Money)¶

In [6]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
fig.set_size_inches(20,8)

sns.set(style="whitegrid")
sns.lineplot(data=data,x=data.Date.dt.month,y="The probability of saving",palette="ch:r=-1,d=.1_r",hue=data.Date.dt.year,linewidth=2, ax=ax)
ax.set_title("The probability of saving (next 12 months period)")
ax.set_xlabel("Months")

plt.show()

As seen above graph shows monthly distribution of Probability of saving money of each year between 2014 and 2022. years are indicated by colors dark green to light pink in ascending order. It can be understood from legend.

Note : there is a half line and it shows 2022.

When having a look I could not realize any obvious seasonlity. I am seeing sharp increases in March, April and October months. Also, Saving habits tend to increase towards to recent years. These are all take-aways from this graph because it seems to be randomly distributed.

Autocorrelation Graphs¶

In [8]:
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf

plot_acf(data["The probability of saving"],title="Saving Money")
plt.show()

plot_acf(data["The probability of borrowing money"],title="Borrowing Money")
plt.show()

The main goal to plot autocorrelation function is to see whether they have any seasonal patterns that I could not realize. However, as assumed they don't exhibit any seasonal pattern.

Main take-away can be that we have proved they are highly autocorrelated attributes until the approximately 15 lags.

As seen in the heatmap all relationships are covered in previous section. Also, it is unexpected situation that the probability of saving has no significant relationship with Consumer Loan and zam. Let's go to conclusion part.

Last Words¶

When starting to the analysis I was expecting Probability of borrowing money and Probability of saving has negative correlation because saving seems positive action and borrowing seems negative action. On the contrary, they have positive correlation. After comparing both of them I saw that Probability of borrowing money has more meaning than the other. Therefore, I prefered to only compare borrowing money habits with zam,USD/TRY, and Consumer Loan. Not surprisingly, people consider borrowing money when dollar increase. However, Interest rate(Consumer Loan Rate) has not effect on borrowing money habits as much as dollar has.

Also, when idea of borrowing money increase "zam" searches on google increase, because both of them are highly correlated with dollar rate.

In a nutshell, common correlation component is USD/TRY exchange rate. It has important effect on Turkish people's habits. Also, Borrowing Money that my search point has significant relation with dollar ,interest rate ,and zam
